Let me start with a quick question: When you move houses, would you carry all the boxes and furniture yourself, or would you call professional movers?

Most of us would call movers—because they know how to pack, load, and transport things efficiently, no matter how big or fragile. That’s exactly what DT does for our data. 
It’s our Python-based, fully cloud-native framework that specializes in transferring data across different databases—Oracle, SQL Server, Postgres, and more—without us worrying about the heavy lifting.

To make this real, let’s look at some numbers. When we transfer Oracle-to-Oracle using traditional CSV exports with SQL Loader, we manage about 30–50k rows per second. 
It works, but imagine trying to move an entire house one box at a time—it quickly becomes slow and painful. With Datatran on Spark, it’s like calling an entire fleet of movers instead of just one truck. 
We can scale horizontally and move hundreds of thousands of rows per second, cutting jobs that used to take hours down to minutes, with reliability, error handling, and logging built in.

So in short, Datatran is our professional moving service for data—making sure it gets from point A to point B quickly, safely, and at the scale we need in the cloud.
